<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Bundled fallback for the Project Gutenberg Source. Gutenberg has no
  favicon-friendly branding to fetch at runtime (gutendex.com is the API mirror,
  not the user-visible face), so this monogram is what every surface renders —
  the "Add source" picker card, the Settings Sources row, and the drawer entry.

  Design: burgundy circle background, white open-book icon at the center. The
  book glyph is the Material `menu_book` outline path, scaled and centered in a
  24-unit viewport — a well-known "public library" affordance that reads clearly
  at 24dp (drawer/switcher rows) and 40dp (picker card).
-->
